30/09/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- European Commission Vice President responsible for Justice, Freedom and Security issues Jacques Barrot and Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic voiced expectation Tuesday (September 29th) that Montenegrin citizens will enjoy visa-free travel to EU member states, staring in January. 
Barrot, who arrived in Podgorica from Belgrade, told a press conference that an EU mission of experts will visit Montenegro in mid-October to assess the country's progress in meeting necessary criteria. 
(RTCG, RTS - 29/09/09)
